import app from './src/config/api'
import 'dotenv/config'

const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000

app.listen(3000, () => console.log(`Server rodando na porta ${PORT}`))

import express from 'express'

import router from '../routes'

const app = express()

app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: true }))
app.use(express.json())

app.use(router)

export default app

import express from 'express'
import crtlUsers from './users/user.controllers'

const router = express.Router()

//Users
router.get('/users/', crtlUsers.get)
router.get('/user/:id/', crtlUsers.getById)
router.post('/user/', crtlUsers.post)
router.put('/user/:id/', crtlUsers.update)
router.delete('/user/:id/', crtlUsers.delete)

export default router

import db from 'mongoose'
import dotenv from 'dotenv'

dotenv.config()

db.connect(process.env.DBURI)
.then(res => console.log(`Conectado ao banco de dados com sucesso em "${process.env.DBURI}"`))
.catch(err => console.error(`Erro ao conectar ao banco de dados: ${err}`))
